<p class="line">
<br>
<p class="para">-A
Beautiful Song-</p>
<br>
<p class="title">The
Bunker that was our home fell. The council of Humanity we believed in
was a lie. Herein lies a record that has never been disclosed: A
record of sights witnessed by 2B and 9S within a memory. Sights seen
as they travelled a world mired in absurdity and deceit.</p>
<p class="line">
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama (narration)
– </span></p><p class="para">The bunker, a satellite base suspended in orbit, has
fallen. With 9S having lost the only home he's ever known, one woman
represents his last ray of light.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">Where the hell is 2B!?</p>
<br>
<p class="para"><p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153:</span></p><p class="para">Scanning. Black box signal located.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">Put it on the map!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153:</span></p><p class="para">Alert: Large-scale ground tremors detected. Underground soil
structure is no longer stable. Cause is likely a high-magnitude
earthquake. Proposal: Evacuate immediately.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">I'm not going anywhere!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama (narration):</span></p><p class="para">Perhaps some part of him already knows. Perhaps he
should give up. But he continues to run, as though trying to escape a
curse that clings to him like mud.</p>
<br>
<p class="para">[Panting
as 9S runs]</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">2B... 2B...</p>
<br>
<p class="para">[Panting
as he runs, then stopping]</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">2B! Are you...Ah!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama (narration):</span></p><p class="para">
The sight before him is so unbelievable, he wishes he
could avert his eyes. A scarlet-soaked blade pierces her body. He
denies it with his whole being. He denies the visual data captured by
his sensors. He denies the conclusions yielded by logical
consideration of the situation. He denies the very reality unfolding
before him.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">Oh no... 2B... No...</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama (narration):</span></p><p class="para">She was his last ray of light. His precious
hope that must never be lost.</p>
<br>
<p class="para">[9S
wails. Groaning and screaming] 
</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">A2! I'll kill you!<br/>
<br/>

</p>
<p class="title">Act
1: A City Without Memories</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">2B! 2B! Where are we...? Pod, do a scan of the surrounding
terrain. ...Pod? Pod, do you copy!?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama (narration):</span></p><p class="para">The spacious expanse where 9S finds himself is eerily
quiet. His voice scatters and disappears into the ether as he speaks.
He is surrounded by a vast city robbed of color. White buildings are
covered by an all-devouring canopy of pure white that blankets the
sky.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042:</span></p><p class="para"> Scan complete. Target verified as YoRHa unit 9S,</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">Pod 042, where is 2B!?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042:</span></p><p class="para"> Unknown. We were separated during the collapse.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">Dammit... Scan for her black-box signal!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042:</span></p><p class="para"> Alert: Scanning impossible. Communications in the vicinity
have been jammed.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">Because of the EMP blasts? I've gotta find 2B right away!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042:</span></p><p class="para"> Excessive activity detected in the thought-control node of
YoRHa unit 9S. Proposal: Cool system by way of short-term sleep.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">Pass.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama (narration):</span></p><p class="para">Red flashes through 9S's mind. It is the color of a
cold blade thrust into a soft stomach. The crimson liquid that seeps
from it. He sees the gentle look in 2B's eyes as she calls him Nines
in her last moments.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">Use sensors to perform a scan of the periphery!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042:</span></p><p class="para"> Analysis: No organic heat signatures or movement detected.
However, the precision of this information is 39.1% lower than normal
as it is not possible to connect to the network.</p>
<br>
<p class="para">Mama
(narration)– Suppressing his urge to scream, 9S looks out over the
mysterious space before him.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">I'm going to look for 2B.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042:</span></p><p class="para"> That action is not recommended. There is a 98.254% chance
that YoRHa unit 2B has perished.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">I don't care what the odds are.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042:</span></p><p class="para"> Proposal: YoRHa unit 9S should prioritize escaping this area.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">You can leave if you want. I'll look for her alone.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042:</span></p><p class="para"> Tactical Support Units are not permitted to act independently
of their assigned YoRHa units. Furthermore, there is a small chance
additional information may be learned regarding YoRHa unit 2B. For
these reasons, this Pod will accompany YoRHa unit 9S.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">Suit yourself.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama (narration):</span></p><p class="para">He is caught in a cycle of despair. No prayer will be
answered. The future remains closed as time continues to flow. 9S
understands perfectly. He knows she does not exist within his reach.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">Like I'd give up that easily...</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama (narration):</span></p><p class="para">Someone who has yet to mourn a loss could not
possibly say farewell. A black shadow dashes through the white
expanse. He must say farewell, even if it destroys his creaking
heart.</p>
<p class="line">
<br>
<p class="para">[A2
groaning]</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042 (narration):</span></p><p class="para">Despite being caught in the collapse of the city
ruins, A2 made it through intact.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">Nnngh... god...dammit! Move, you piece of junk!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042 (narration):</span></p><p class="para">She awakens to a body in great pain from head to
toe. A body that will not do as she commands. Spewing abuses in
disdain of this development, A2 manages to rise to her feet.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">Where the hell am I?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042 (narration):</span></p><p class="para">Cold white buildings are lined throughout the
space. Hollow light pours down from an impossibly clear sky. As A2
takes a step, something emerges from a nearby box.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">...A hologram?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042 (narration):</span></p><p class="para">The three-dimensional image of a robot wearing a
hat bows in A2's direction. Then, as if on cue, machines in the area
awaken one after the other. Their speakers blare the same phrase
repeatedly, as if attempting to brainwash the listener. A light
attached to a building projects an image on the ground. It is what
was referred to in the old world as an “advertisement.”</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">Buzz off, you freakin' scrapheaps!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042 (narration):</span></p><p class="para">Without a second thought, A2 launches an
offensive, scattering fragments of destroyed machines across the
ground.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">That should shut things up around here... Huh?</p>
<br>
<p class="para">[Cheerful
humming - Emil's Shop song]</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042 (narration):</span></p><p class="para">A2 hears an easygoing song that fits poorly with
her surroundings, as well as the piercing sound of an engine. Though
far away, it gradually draws closer.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">Seriously?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil:</span></p><p class="para">Oh no, somebody's in the way! Better pump the brakes and stop on
the double!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042 (narration):</span></p><p class="para">As A2 worries the shrill sound of braking may
have shattered her eardrums, the odor of burnt rubber assaults her
nasal passages.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">What a stench!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil:</span></p><p class="para">S-sorry...</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042 (narration):</span></p><p class="para">A bizarre face is attached to the body of an aged
car. Though its appearance is suspicious, A2 doesn't seem wary in the
slightest.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">Emil. What are you doing here?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil:</span></p><p class="para">So the city suddenly collapsed, right? And then these big white
buildings shot straight up from the ground like BOOM! I tried to
escape by jumping across collapsing footholds, but I didn't have the
horsepower.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">I see.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil:</span></p><p class="para">It was pretty crazy! ...Hey, where are you going?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">I'm gonna blow this joint. Being surrounded by noisy-ass machines
isn't my thing.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil:</span></p><p class="para">Then let me tag along! I can't get any business done down here
anyway. You don't mind, right?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">Makes no difference to me. If you can't keep up, I'll just leave
you behind anyway.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042 (narration):</span></p><p class="para">They are amidst a sea of perfectly white
buildings. In both shape and form, it is an exact replica of a human
city from the old world. Skyscrapers that stand among the clouds.
Highways which stretch in all directions. Deluges of light and
information. An uninhabited city filled with objects symbolizing
humanity's prosperity. And now, A2 and Emil wander this unfamiliar
place in search of a way out.</p>
<p class="line">
<br>
<p class="title">-Peaceful
Sleep- <br/>
<br/>

</p>
<br>
<p class="para">-City
Ruins-</p>
<br>
<p class="para">2003
– 12 – A strange disease of unknown origin emerges, one which
causes people to turn white and transform into salt. It begins to
spread like wildfire. 
</p>
<br>
<p class="para">2025
– 01 – A technology is discovered that enables the separation and
preservation of a human's body and soul.</p>
<br>
<p class="para">2061
– 12 – The process of separating humans is completed. It is
decided that humanity will wait until a treatment for the disease has
been found.</p>
<br>
<p class="para">5012
– 08 – Aliens from outer space invade and launch an attack across
the entire planet.</p>
<br>
<p class="para">11732
– 03 – A large-scale counteroffensive staged by the androids
managing Earth ends in failure.</p>
<br>
<p class="para">11940
– 12 – To bring an end to the deadlocked war, the newest models
of androids are assembled to form an organization called “YoRHa.”</p>
<p class="line">
<p class="title">Part
2: An Encounter Forgotten</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil:</span></p><p class="para">No matter how far we go, all the buildings look the same.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">I'm sick of walking around like a chump. You've got gunpowder,
right? Let's blast our way through.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil:</span></p><p class="para">How about we take a look in that direction this time? We might
find something,</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">Did you not hear me? Where's the gunpowder at? Let's get
explode-y.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil:</span></p><p class="para">What fantastic weather! Not a cloud in the sky.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">Quit acting like you don't hear me, you rusty jalopy.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 (narration)
– </span></p><p class="para"> Footsteps and the sound of an engine echo through
the colorless, empty city. But while the strange sights may be eerie,
the city doesn't once bare its fangs at the pair. Yet A2 still moves
to grasp her weapon. She points the blade at the space Between two
buildings, towards an alley shrouded in shadow.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">All right. The hell are you following us around for?</p>
<br>
<p class="para">Emil
- ...A2?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 (narration)
– </span></p><p class="para"> A bundle of white cloth suspended in midair
emerges from the alley. The cloth has two black holes in the spots
that would normally contain eyes, but no emotion can be gleaned from
the openings. And then...the cloth speaks.</p>
<br>
<p class="para"><p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama:</span></p><p class="para"> Wipe that sour look off your face. Mama's not your enemy.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 (narration)
– </span></p><p class="para"> A2's blade remains pointed at the white cloth,
still as a glacier.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">...Doesn't seem like a machine to me.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil:</span></p><p class="para">Sure is spooky though. Kinda looks like a ghost.</p>
<br>
<p class="para"><p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama:</span></p><p class="para"> Goodness! If you ask Mama, you look quite odd yourself.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil:</span></p><p class="para">Wha--!? No way! My body's just been optimized for its purpose!
What's so weird about that!?</p>
<br>
<p class="para"><p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama:</span></p><p class="para"> Optimization and good looks can go hand in hand, child. Take me
for an example.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">Hold still. You make even the slightest movement I don't like,
and I'll cut you down. Also, what's with this “Mama” crap? Whose
mom are you supposed to be?</p>
<br>
<p class="para"><p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama:</span></p><p class="para"> Everyone's! I'm everyone's Mama!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil:</span></p><p class="para">Mess her up, A2! Even if she's not a machine, She's definitely up
to no good!</p>
<br>
<p class="para"><p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama:</span></p><p class="para"> Hold on now! Mama's not up to anything! Look, I'll put my hands
in the air for you. If you want, I'll even spin around three time and
yell “Mama!”</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">Have you no shame? Shit.</p>
<br>
<p class="para"><p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama:</span></p><p class="para"> Mama's fine doing what it takes to stay alive.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 (narration)
– </span></p><p class="para"> After a brief pause, an exasperated A2 lowers her
blade.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">You got a name?</p>
<br>
<p class="para"><p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama:</span></p><p class="para"> Just call me Mama, child.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">You live here?</p>
<br>
<p class="para"><p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama:</span></p><p class="para"> Oh no. Mama's come a long, long way to serve as your guide.</p>
<p class="line">
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 (narration)
– </span></p><p class="para"> The city of pure white expands uninterrupted into
infinity, and 9S presses through it without a clear goal in mind. 
</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">2B! If you hear me, send out a signal...</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042:</span></p><p class="para"> Signal detection impossible due to prolonged jamming of
communications. This Pod recommends securing an escape route.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 (narration)
– </span></p><p class="para"> 9S does not respond to the Pod. He just continues
on, chasing the shadow of the person he seeks.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">Where the hell are we?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 (narration)
– </span></p><p class="para"> 9S see's half-broken fencing, as well as empty
boxes strewn across the floor. The bottles on the shelves have
fallen, causing many of them to break. Like the other buildings, this
one is colored entirely white. However, it looks different—almost
like a ruin.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042:</span></p><p class="para"> This area resembles what those in the old world called a
“supermarket.” Humans used it as a facility for purchasing daily
necessities.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 (narration)
– </span></p><p class="para"> There is something unusual about the ruins of a
commercial facility juxtaposed against the rest of the orderly city.
However, 9S immediately loses interest, for he has far more pressing
matters to attend to.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">What would 2B do in this situation?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 (narration)
– </span></p><p class="para"> Some possibilities could be derived from the data
accumulated in his memory area. But how valuable would they be in a
city as bizarre as this?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">I'm useless without you...</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 (narration)
– </span></p><p class="para"> He puts himself in 2B's place. He envisions her
in his mind. His body seized by a frigid loneliness, 9S stops in his
tracks. 
</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042:</span></p><p class="para"> Alert: Movement detected on sensors.</p>
<br>
