<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 (narration):</span></p><p class="para">Moving like a flickering flame, the shadow quickly
adopts the form of a young child. Its eyes hold not anger, nor
hatred, no sadness, instead shining with a faint, innocent light.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier:</span></p><p class="para">Oh, I see... Yonah... you've been right there...all along.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">The door flies open on its own, as though unleashing the souls
trapped behind it. A pane of stained glass deep within the shrine
shines warmly as it filters sunlight from the outside.</p>
<br>
<p class="para"><p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama:</span></p><p class="para"> That stained glass is the escape port.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153:</span></p><p class="para">Based on how much time remains until this space collapses,
only our consciousness data can be sent.</p>
<br>
<p class="para"><p class="title"><span class="title-box">Mama:</span></p><p class="para"> That's right. I'm afraid you'll have to leave the memories you
made here behind.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">You first, 2B.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">Not waiting for an answer, 9S grabs 2B's hand and tries to take
her to the stained glass—but 2B gently shakes it off.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B:
</span></p><p class="para">I'm sorry, 9S.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">What are you apologizing for?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B:
</span></p><p class="para">You know whats going on, don't you? I died when the city
collapsed. What you see now is patched together from data fragments
on the network.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">So what? Even if you ARE just patched data, you're still 2B!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 (narration):</span></p><p class="para">Were he capable of mourning the death of someone he
cherished. He could simply say farewell. But faced with the phantom
of what has been lost, his modest wish swells out of proportion. No
matter what she hears, 2B simple listens with a troubled smile. 9S
understands the situation perfectly, but that doesn't mean he's
capable of stopping himself.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">It's okay if you don't remember anything once we get out! We'll
start over from the beginning, just like you've always done for me!
And this time I'll... I'll be the one who saves you!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">He offers prayers he knows will go unheard. For if he fails to do
even that, all will be swallowed by despair.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B:
</span></p><p class="para">No, 9S. My body doesn't exist anymore. There's nowhere for my
data to go.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">We can't know what'll happen unless we try!</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B:
</span></p><p class="para">But I WANT to disappear here. If entering the port means
discarding my memories, I'd rather hold onto my time with you and-- 
</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">You think I feel any different!?</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2:</span></p><p class="para">Created to fight and existing only to die, the pair were joined
by a faint light in the most absurd of circumstances.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">9S:</span></p><p class="para">I'm going to stay. If you're going to disappear, I want to stay
with you until the very end.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B:</span></p><p class="para">...Thank you, 9S.</p>
<br>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 (narration):</span></p><p class="para">The gentle smile on her lips is proof of her
rejection. It's a smile born of wanting to protect someone who they
had unexpectedly come to cherish more than anything in the world.</p>
